The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Roy best

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Subhrajit Roy was adjudged the best athlete of the 45th ABP Annual Sports, held at the Mohammedan Sporting on Sunday. 

He won both 100m and 200m races. 

The event witnessed a record number of more than 700 participants this year. 

The Advertising and Marketing department won the tug of war event by outplaying Administration department. Circulation department emerged third. 

From next year retired employees can compete in a 50m race. 




